block.p: Elizabeth Babson Carter, a daughter of Dr. and Mrs. D. Martin Carter of New York, was married yesterday in Guilford, Conn., to Lieut. Timothy Brian Rooney, the son of Mr. and Mrs. Thomas F. Rooney of West Redding, Conn. The Revs. Anna and David Carter Florence, the bride's sister and brother-in-law, performed the Presbyterian ceremony at the First Congregational Church.

Mrs. Rooney, 22 years old, graduated from Dartmouth College and is studying for a master's degree in education at the College of William & Mary. Her father is a professor of medicine and a senior physician at Rockefeller University. Her mother, Anne Babson Carter, is a poet.

Elizabeth Babson Carter, a daughter of Dr. and Mrs. D. Martin Carter of New York, was married yesterday in Guilford, Conn., to Lieut. Timothy Brian Rooney, the son of Mr. and Mrs. Thomas F. Rooney of West Redding, Conn. The Revs. Anna and David Carter Florence, the bride's sister and brother-in-law, performed the Presbyterian ceremony at the First Congregational Church.

Mrs. Rooney, 22 years old, graduated from Dartmouth College and is studying for a master's degree in education at the College of William & Mary. Her father is a professor of medicine and a senior physician at Rockefeller University. Her mother, Anne Babson Carter, is a poet.

Lieutenant Rooney, 27, is a Navy fighter pilot at the Oceana Naval Air Station in Virginia Beach, Va. He graduated from Dartmouth. His mother, Sandra Rooney, owns the Petite Collector, a women's specialty shop in Westport, Conn. His father is a pilot for Trans World Airlines.
